✅ It will look something like this in code view:
Message Id: @{triggerOutputs()?['body/Id']}
That’s it!
You don’t have to manually type it — just pick Message Id from dynamic content.
Step 3: Continue with Extraction
Now, use this Get email (V3) step’s Body output in your regex expressions:
For Position Code:
first(match(outputs('Get_email_(V3)')?['body/Body'], '\d{8}'))
For Hyperlink:
first(match(outputs('Get_email_(V3)')?['body/Body'], '(?i)(?<=<a href=")([^"]+)(?=">Click here)'))
🧩 Quick Summary
Step	Action	Field	What to set
1	When a new email arrives (V3)	Folder, etc.	As per your need
2	Get email (V3)	Message Id	Choose Message Id from step 1
3	Compose	Expression	Extract 8-digit Position Code
4	Compose	Expression	Extract “Click here” link
5	Add row to Excel	Map outputs	From Compose steps
